A super hot summer day and I stop into this refreshingly air conditioned cafe to grab a mid morning snack after just coming in on the train. I had a panini and it was awesome!!!! The place was busy for 10:30 in the morning and visited by locals and regulars. That's how I knew the Avanti's was a great place. Lot's of choices on the board and I wished I had more time to try more of them. If you're in town, check this out for lunch, you won't be disappointed.

We liked everything about this casual small place - fresh food, affordable prices, quick pleasant service. Sandwiches and paninis are huge and tasty, choice of salads. Generous portions of meat and other fillings. Good espresso drinks. Felt authentic and simple. Seems to be very popular with business crowd. We popped in for a quick breakfast after visiting Willis Tower. OMG! The food was delicious and the cappuccino perfect!! The staff was excellent, kind and courteous. So glad we stopped.
Good, quick and tasty food... a great go to spot!
